    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-08-17T18:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-08-17T18:45:00-05:00" n="17"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d17">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">855A.24/50: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador to the Belgian Government in Exile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Biddle</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">at London</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-17T19:45:00-04:00"
                            >August 17, 1942—7:45 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–22. Department’s airgram A–17, August 12. Department informed that export
                    duties have recently been increased in Belgian <pb facs="0025" n="19"
                        xml:id="pg_19"/> Congo on palm nuts and oil of geranium. Please consider
                    advisability of suggesting paragraph in tripartite agreement providing that
                    Congo export duties shall not be increased during term of agreement on
                    commodities listed in the agreement as of interest to us.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
